    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName><name type="cognomen" key="Primigenius"><supplied reason="lost">Pr</supplied>imigenio</name></persName>
                    <lb n="2"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>the
                    <lb n="3"/><expan><abbr><supplied reason="lost">co</supplied>ntub<supplied reason="lost">ern</supplied>al</abbr><ex>i</ex></expan>
                    <lb n="4"/><supplied reason="lost">e</supplied>t sibi
                </ab>
            </div>
            
            <div type="translation">
            <p>For Primigenius, [---]the, for her/his companion and for herself/himself.</p></div>

            <div type="commentary">
            <p>"Primigenio" is dative, and "contubernali" an apposition to it: Primigenius is
                    identifies as the dedicator's contubernalis. The dedicator's name is lost; the
                    "et sibi" element indicates the monument was also made for the dedicant.</p></div>
            

